5. Speed, Stability, and Compression Gains

A. Speed

Using vectors/matrices instead of symbol chains reduces cognitive steps by 10–50×.

B. Compression

Tensor contraction collapses complex meaning into minimal coherent structure.

Example:

T_{ijk} \rightarrow v_i

Entire story arc → single intention vector.

C. Stability

Curvature measures emotional/narrative tension; negative curvature stabilizes.

D. Predictive Power

Gradients and Hessians reveal where the narrative will drift next.

E. Entropy Control

Divergence = leakage
Curl = confusion
Laplacian = calm

PantheonOS can measure and fix these.

